Maybe we can prepare the options as an array and then concatenate `shadow` options on? Then, attach the path parameters after all the options are read.

``` js
var diffOptions = [
  '-verbose',
  '-metric', 'RMSE',
  '-highlight-color', 'RED'
];
if (options.shadow) {
  diffOptions = diffOptions.concat([
    '-dissimilarity-threshold', '1'
  ]);
} else {
  diffOptions = diffOptions.concat([
    '-compose', 'Src'
  ]);
}

var diffArgs = diffOptions.concat([
  options.actualPath,
  options.expectedPath,
  // If there is no output image, then output to `stdout` (which is ignored)
  options.diffPath || '-'
]);
```

